<br>
Back when FV first opened, and no one could speak any language other than their racial ones, and languages were bugged so that you couldn't learn more than five points in any other language <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>but no one knew that</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and you could only learn one point per real-time hour anyway so people took forever to catch on, we all had this little problem.  Even when we knew that, and those poor suckers who didn't know that were trying to group with us to exchange language lessons, we couldn't explain it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>the very old</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> FV work-around was to have messages written in your description box, so that when people inspected you they could read them.  But there's very little space there, so there were all kinds of people walking around with messages in their description boxes sending people to this board so they could read about the languages bug and know what was going on.<br>
<br>
I was one of those people.  I imagine it's getting to be a pretty tight crowd that still remembers those days.  If that was you, my best regards.  I remember I wanted to tear my hair out over that languages bug sometimes (Sony tells us &quot;all is working as intended....&quot;) but somehow I can still get nolstalgic.<br>
<br>
Take care,<br>
Val <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.utsc.utoronto.ca/~02rybakj/Valquisssig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyntercrystalbow>Wynter Crystalbow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/03 5:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4686.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rolecall...the real old-timers</span><hr size=1> Actually didn't take long before we figured out how to break the one hour rule anyway.  And we caught on that languages were broken at that point.  We didn't catch it during the test run since characters were temporary and nobody wanted to take the time to test the languages at that point.  And being an aspiring mistress of languages, it still all irritated me beyond all heck.<br>
<br>
I'm remembering more what a pain the alignment bugs were.  No matter how compatible your alignments were, you had to form groups several times in certain unknown orders if someone went LD and tried to come back.<br>
<br>
I miss those days at times though.  The way things are nowadays it's really meaningless being a language master here.  It used to mean something back in the day I was one of the few language masters around.  You actually took the effort to ping pong every exotic language off someone else to teach each other things.  Still, it's nice to know I helped to spread the exotics.<br>
<br>
It's even easier now since you don't even have to zone to ping pong languages since the skill points update without zoning.<br>
<br>
Listen to me blab.  *giggles*  Next you know I'm going to be griping how we had to go hunt the orc pawns in six foot snow uphill both ways, and the orc pawns were all much more powerful in that day, and all these youngsters don't know how good they have it.<br>
<br>
